{
  "texts": [
    "In conclusion, VERIFINER is robust in diverse low-resource scenarios within the biomedical domain, where the scarcity of available datasets has remained as a long-standing challenge.",
    "Named Entity Recognition.",
    "A conventional approach for solving NER task is to predict probability distribution of entity types and sequentially label each token (Jeong and Kang, 2023; Lee et al., 2019).",
    "In domain-specific NER, data scarcity challenge has been a consistent challenge.",
    "Recent works attempt to solve the issue with data augmentation (Chen et al., 2021; Zhou et al., 2022)."
  ]
}